From Creamer Media in Johannesburg, this is the Real Economy Report. Sashnee Moodley: Generator manufacturer Himoinsa has opened its sales and service facility in Midrand to more effectively serve its rental customers and to provide immediate power to clients while customised power systems are manufactured for their specific applications. Schalk Burger has the story. Schalk Burger: Himoinsa Southern Africa has established its sales and service facility in Midrand, Gauteng, in addition to its bonded warehouse in Port Elizabeth, to meet the demand for its rental fleet. It provides generators for large projects, for temporary applications and as stand-in systems while bespoke engineered generators are built for the clients. Himoinsa Southern Africa business development director Matt Bell gives more insight into the company’s rental and permanent generation offerings in Southern Africa. Himoinsa Southern Africa business development director Matt Bell: Sashnee Moodley: Other news making headlines Ring-fence Eskom’s ‘bad bank’ generation assets, says energy expert A leading electricity expert is warning that there is little or no prospect that Eskom can trade itself out of its current financial difficulties and that restructuring is now both urgent and practically implementable. University of Cape Town Graduate School of Business’ Professor Anton Eberhard: Sashnee Moodley: That’s Creamer Media’s Real Economy Report. Join us again next week for more news and insight into South Africa’s real economy.